  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is the second phase of a partnership between Lutheran World Relief (LWR), the Gold Fields mining company and the Centro  Ecum&#xE9;nico de Promoci&#xF3;n y Acci&#xF3;n Social Norte (CEDEPAS Norte) to improve rural incomes in the Hualgayoc district of Peru&#x2019;s Cajamarca department.

LWR, Gold Fields and CEDEPAS believe that stabilizing and increasing farm incomes is the key to building resilience and preventing catastrophic de-capitalization of rural farmers in the face of increasing climate shocks in this sensitive high-Andean production system.

The project addresses two central problems: insufficient rural incomes, and inefficient investment of public funds in basic services, both of which contribute to the cycle of poverty in the district.</narrative>
  </description>
